## Evolution

This document evolves through the project lifecycle:
- **Created by:** `/pbr:new-project` during project initialization
- **Updated by:** `/pbr:discuss-phase` when scope or constraints change
- **Frozen after:** Roadmap creation -- subsequent changes require explicit scope-change discussion via `/pbr:discuss-phase`

## Quality Criteria

A good PROJECT.md satisfies:
- [ ] Core value is one sentence, under 20 words
- [ ] What This Is answers: what, who, why in 2-3 sentences
- [ ] Every In Scope item maps to at least one REQ-ID in REQUIREMENTS.md
- [ ] Every Out of Scope item has a rationale
- [ ] Success criteria are observable and testable
- [ ] Key Decisions table has at least one entry
- [ ] Constraints section is populated (even if "none identified")
{{#brownfield}}
- [ ] Validated Requirements cite evidence from existing code
- [ ] Existing Architecture references codebase scan files
{{/brownfield}}
